<p>I need to write functions like this:</p>  <pre><code>void foo() {     //some details } enum fun_names {     fun_name_foo, }; </code></pre>  <p>So I made 2 macros:</p>  <pre><code>#define MAKE_FUN(fun) void fun(){} #define ADD_FUN(fun) fun_name_##fun, </code></pre>  <p>Then use them like this:</p>  <pre><code>MAKE_FUN(foo) MAKE_FUN(bar) enum fun_names {     ADD_FUN(foo)     ADD_FUN(bar) }; </code></pre>  <p>But as you can see, I'm repeating 2 macros with exactly same arguments. Is it possible to make one single macro like this?</p>  <pre><code>CREATE_FUN(foo) CREATE_FUN(bar) </code></pre>  <p>This saves lines of codes and is less error-prone.</p>